cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about indoor semantic segmentation using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of residual modules and skip-connections is a common technique in deep learning (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The incorporation of depth information also involves robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE) research. Therefore, these sub-categories are likely to be relevant to this paper.
